content.description: Make a weird /awkward pull up from the sit, move left to the high with your hands in the seam and poor feet, and move left to the top. Dealing with the feet is the crux. It is sort of a 1.5 star route.
content.protection: A pad. It has a good land landing and is not tall.
content.location: This ascends the obvious right arete.

content.description: Sit start using cool handholds, and make an awkward move onto the slopey arete. Bad feet complicate this one too. It is harder than the other arete.
content.protection: A pad. It has a good landing.
content.location: It ascends the obvious left arete.

content.description: This a decent, lone boulder right on a little point surrounded by the ocean on three sides. I think it is still granite, but the rock of little atypical for the area (more reminiscent of some of the Dogtown Boulders).
